## 📇 API Documentation

| Method | Endpoint | Description | Authentication |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **POST** | `/api/register` | Register a new user account | None |
| **POST** | `/api/login` | Log in and receive a Sanctum token | None |
| **POST** | `/api/logout` | Revoke the current access token | Bearer Token |
| **GET** | `/api/user` | Fetch the current authenticated profile | Bearer Token |
| **GET** | `/api/products` | Retrieve all products (supports `search` & `page`) | Bearer Token |
| **POST** | `/api/products` | Create a new product entry | Bearer Token |
| **GET** | `/api/products/{id}` | Retrieve details of a single product | Bearer Token |
| **PUT** | `/api/products/{id}` | Update details of a product | Bearer Token |
| **DELETE**| `/api/products/{id}` | Delete a product entry | Bearer Token |

---

## 📬 Postman Integration

A fully configured Postman collection is supplied at:
📁 [`Product_Management_API.postman_collection.json`](file:///c:/wamp64/www/Product-Management-Api/Product_Management_API.postman_collection.json)

**How to Import:**
1. Open Postman.
2. Click **Import** in the upper left.
3. Select the `Product_Management_API.postman_collection.json` file in the root.
4. Execute queries. Successful logins will script-save the token value automatically to your workspace variables.

---

## 🧪 Testing and Verification

To execute all automated unit/feature tests (covering status codes, payload shapes, and db states):
```bash
php artisan test
```
All 24 tests covering auth and product workflows should report successful execution status.
